{{see|Virus}}
==English==

===Etymology===
The word '''virus''' is derived from the [[Latin]] ''virus'', meaning roughly “poison”, “slime” or “venom”.

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-aɪrəs|-aɪrəs]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun|es}}

# A core of [[DNA]] or [[RNA]] surrounded by a [[protein]] coat that requires a living cell to [[replicate]] &mdash; often causes disease in the host organism.
# A [[computer virus]].
# Something [[evil]] or corrupting which has the ability to spread throughout its environment.  Some examples are alien organisms (those transported to a new region where they compete with and eventually overwhelm the original organisms), or in the case of many [[pessimistic]] people, [[humanity]] as a whole for its spread across the globe without care for the [[sustainability]] of the [[environment]].

===External links===
*An article on the [[Wikipedia:Plural of virus|plural of ''virus'']].

